{"title_page": "Indigenous people in video games", "text_new": "[[Indigenous people]] have a long history of collaborating on the creation of [[video game]]s.<ref name=\"vimeo.com\">https://vimeo.com/128110465</ref> It has only been with the release of [[Never Alone (video game)|Never Alone]] though that broad media attention has been paid to these projects.<ref>A Tribe Called Geek's third podcast called \"Indigenous Gaming\" http://atribecalledgeek.com/tag/video-games/ ; see also http://ca.ign.com/articles/2015/01/16/the-rise-of-indigenous-storytelling-in-games</ref> There have been a growing number of game gatherings and community organizing around Indigenous games happening in the United States, Canada, and New Zealand.<ref name=\"linkedin.com\">https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/natives-game-dev-gathering-elizabeth-lapens%C3%A9e</ref><ref name=\"pinnguaq.com\">http://pinnguaq.com/blog-all/120-evening-celebrate</ref> Indigenous creators of video games have been featured in the DIGITAL MEDIA ART+CADE as part of imagineNATIVE<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.imaginenative.org/home/node/4546 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927051603/http://www.imaginenative.org/home/node/4546 |archive-date=2015-09-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and in ''Memories of the Future/Souvenirs du futur'' at SAW Video Media Art Centre in Ottawa.<ref>http://www.sawvideo.com/event/memories-future</ref> Many early video games that depicted Indigenous people misrepresented them and perpetuated negative stereotypes (see [[Custer's Revenge]]).<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/aboriginal/indigenous-video-game-designer-takes-stand-against-custer-s-revenge-1.2851104</ref> Video games created by Indigenous people enable the creators to self-determine how they are represented<ref>http://www.content.alternative.ac.nz/index.php/alternative/article/view/274</ref>.\n\n== Games where Indigenous people represent themselves ==\nIndigenous people have been involved in a range of projects where they have the opportunity to depict themselves. These games range in the style of the collaboration from games that consult with a single Indigenous person to games that are entirely developed and designed by Indigenous people.<ref name=\"vimeo.com\"/>  \n* [[Aboriginal Peoples Television Network]] ([http://animism.com/ Animism] [2010] [http://www.elizabethlapensee.com/#/games/ Mawisowin] [2012], and [http://yourmix.ca/trackjumper.html Your Mix])<ref name=\"elizabethlapensee.com\">http://www.elizabethlapensee.com/#/games/</ref>\n*Aboriginal Territories in Cyberspace [http://www.abtec.org/projects.html Skins Workshops] ([http://skins.abtec.org/skins1.0/ Ots\u00ec:! Rise of the Kanien\u2019keh\u00e1:ka Legends] [2009], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins2.0/ The Adventures of Skahi\u00f2n:hati: Legend of Stone Giant] [2011], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins3.0/ Skahi\u00f2n:hati: Rise of the Kanien\u2019keh\u00e1:ka Legends] [2012], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins4.0/ Ieni\u00e9n:te and the Peacemaker\u2019s Wampum] [2013]<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/aboriginal/story/1.2483001</ref>, [http://skins.abtec.org/skins5.0/ He Ao Hou] [2017], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins6.0/ Wao Kanaka: Realm of the People] [2018])\n* Arviat Code Club ([https://scratch.mit.edu/users/Pinnguaq/ Multiple scratch games] [2014-2015])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pinnguaq.com/nunavut-code-club/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222151058/http://pinnguaq.com/nunavut-code-club/ |archive-date=2015-12-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Black Cherry Digital Productions ([http://www.pathoftheelders.com/index.php Path of the Elders] [2010] in partnership between the Mushkegowuk Cree, Carlton University, and Pinegrove Productions)<ref>http://www.pathoftheelders.com/aboutus</ref> \n* DarianJ ([http://darianj.itch.io/sleep-guardian Sleep Guardian] [2015])<ref>https://www.facebook.com/skins.workshops/?fref=nf</ref>\n* Elizabeth LaPens\u00e9e When Rivers Were Trails [2019], Thunderbird Strike [2017], Coyote Quest [2017] in collaboration with Loretta Todd, Mikan [2017], Honour Water [2016])<ref name=\"elizabethlapensee.com\"/>, Gathering Native Foods [2014] in collaboration with Hibulb Cultural Center, [http://survivance.org/invaders/ Invaders] [2015] with art by Steven Paul Judd and music by [[Trevino Brings Plenty]], [http://www.survivance.org/wesing/ Ninagamomin ji-nanaandawi'iwe] (We Sing for Healing) [2015], Survivance [2011], ([http://www.abtec.org/blog/?p=436 Techno Medicine Wheel] [2008] in collaboration with Cease Wyss \n* Green Circle Productions ([https://manidoonsuglittlespirits.wordpress.com/ Manidoonsug: Little Spirits] [forthcoming] in consultation with Mississauga New Credit and Annishinabe groups around the GTA<ref name=\"pinnguaq.com\"/>\n* Julia Keren-Detar ([http://mushroom11.com/ Mushroom 11])<ref>http://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/nitv-news/article/2017/04/20/video-games-encourage-indigenous-cultural-expression</ref>\n* Minority Media ([http://www.weareminority.com/spirits-of-spring/ Spirits of Spring] [2014])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rezolutionpictures.com/new-cree-video-game-spirits-of-spring-featured-in-best-new-games-on-apple-store-in-over-130-countries/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222103451/http://www.rezolutionpictures.com/new-cree-video-game-spirits-of-spring-featured-in-best-new-games-on-apple-store-in-over-130-countries/ |archive-date=2015-12-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Ogoki ([http://www.ogokilearning.com/native-american-language-apps/ Multiple Language Apps] [2012-2015], [http://www.ogokilearning.com/native-american-language-apps/ Babaamosedaa Let's Go for a Walk] [2014], [http://www.ogokilearning.com/native-american-language-apps/ Brokenhead Bingo] [2015], and [http://www.ogokilearning.com/native-american-language-apps/ Rez Bomb] [2015])<ref>https://itunes.apple.com/ca/developer/ogoki-learning-systems-inc./id477459819</ref> \n* Raindrop Games ([http://www.arrivalgame.com/content/villagekasike.htm Arrival: Village Kasike] [2012] partnered with Roberto Mukaro Borrero and the United Confederation of Taino People<ref>http://uctp.blogspot.ca/2012_11_01_archive.html</ref> \n* Revolve ([http://revolve.ca/work/music-mogul Music Mogul] [2014] with extensive content by Indigenous musicians including [[A Tribe Called Red]], [[Elisapie]], [[Joey Stylez]], [http://music.cbc.ca/#!/artists/Madeskimo Madeskimo], and [[Red City Radio|Red City]]<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/aboriginal/music-mogul-designed-to-teach-indigenous-students-business-skills-1.2944805</ref> \n* [[Upper One Games]] ([[Never Alone (video game)|Never Alone]] [2014])<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/sep/29/never-alone-alaskas-indigenous-game-never-alone-teaches-cooperation-through-stories</ref>\n* [http://virtualsonglines.com.au/ Virtual Songlines] ([http://virtualsonglines.com.au/media/ Irene\u2019s World] [forthcoming], [http://virtualsonglines.com.au/media/ Vincent\u2019s World] [forthcoming], [http://virtualsonglines.com.au/media/ Virtual Warrane II] [forthcoming], [http://virtualsonglines.com.au/media/ Virtual Meanjin] [forthcoming]) \n* [http://www.wisdomoftheelders.org/ Wisdom of the Elders] ([http://survivance.org/ Survivance] [2011])<ref>http://www.neliufpe.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/13.pdf</ref>\n* [http://yijalayala.bighart.org/about/ Yijala Yala Productions], part of [[Big hART]] ([http://www.yijalayala.bighart.org/lovepunks/ Love Punks] [2012])<ref>http://ca.ign.com/articles/2015/01/16/the-rise-of-indigenous-storytelling-in-games</ref>\n* Guilherme Meneses ([https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-news-from-elsewhere-35706657 Huni Kuin] [2016] in a collaboration with the Kanixaw\u00e1 tribe of Brazil and Peru)<ref>http://mashable.com/2016/03/07/indigenous-video-game-huni-kuin/#wH5z.5wtnOqU</ref>\n\n'''Games with Indigenous consultants'''\n* [http://www.7generationgames.com/ 7 Generation Games] ([http://www.7generationgames.com/products/ Spirit Lake] [2013], [http://www.7generationgames.com/products/ Fish Lake] [2015], [http://www.7generationgames.com/products/ Forgotten Trail] [2015], [http://www.7generationgames.com/products/ Aztech Games] [forthcoming])<ref>http://www.7generationgames.com/2013/10/20/our-cultural-consultant-on-cultural-content-in-spirit-lake-the-game/</ref> \n* [http://pinnguaq.com/ Pinnguaq] ([http://pinnguaq.com/singuistics/ Singuistics] [2013], [http://pinnguaq.com/art-alive/ Art Alive] [2015], [http://qalupalik.com/ Qalupalik] [forthcoming])<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/north/pangnirtung-nunavut-game-studio-brings-work-of-pudlo-pudlat-to-life-1.3121713</ref>\n* Ubisoft ([[Assassin's Creed III]] [2012] in consultation with Thomas Deer and voice acting from [[Noah Watts]]<ref>http://www.abtec.org/blog/?p=381</ref>)\n\n== Indigenous people working in game industry == \nIndigenous people work on a range of video game projects from large blockbusters to small indie collaborations. Many of these individuals are also creating other artistic content such as comics, board games, machinima, and fine art.\n\nMany Indigenous people working in video games are running their own studios or solo practices such as [http://www.achimogames.ca Achimostawinan Games], an Indigenous game studio owned and operated by [[M\u00e9tis]] video game designer Meagan Byrne. (Meagan is best known for her work [https://byrneout.itch.io/wanisinowin-lost Wanisinowin | Lost]). Some have been working in the [[Video game industry]] for years, such as [[Allen Turner (game designer)]] and [[John Romero]] ([[Doom (1993 video game)|Doom]]). Some work as both creator and academic, such as design, artist, and writer [[Elizabeth LaPens\u00e9e]] (Anishinaabe and M\u00e9tis), who has had a role in creating games such as When Rivers Were Trails and [https://www.thunderbirdstrike.com/ Thunderbird Strike], which merge interactive media and Indigenous ways of knowing.\n\n* Allen Turner ([[Stubbs the Zombie]], [[Hail to the Chimp]], [[Guilty Party (video game)|Disney's Guilty Party]], Marvel XP)<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/>\n* Ashlee Bird, creator of [https://abird.itch.io/one-small-step One Small Step] and [https://abird.itch.io/imaginenative-gallery-submission Full of Birds]\n* Darrick Glen Baxter, founder of Ogoki (Multiple Language Apps, Alien Bug Attack, Babaamosedaa Let's Go for a Walk, Brokenhead Bingo, Elfs Defence, Rez Bomb, Spike Flyer, Spring Shoes Jump Better)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ogokilearning.com/about-ogoki-learning-systems-learning-president-bio/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222131248/http://www.ogokilearning.com/about-ogoki-learning-systems-learning-president-bio/ |archive-date=2015-12-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Elizabeth LaPens\u00e9e]] (When Rivers Were Trails, Thunderbird Strike, Invaders, Ninagamomin ji-nanaandawi'iwe, Survivance)<ref name=\"elizabethlapensee.com\"/>  \n* Ernest Webb ([[Papo & Yo]], Spirits of Spring)<ref>http://www.nationnews.ca/moving-in-a-new-direction/</ref>\n* Jamie Tucker ([[Lovers in a Dangerous Spacetime]])<ref>https://tworowtimes.com/art-and-culture/first-nations-comics-and-video-games-draw-a-crowd/</ref>\n*[https://www.jesseholt.com/ Jesse Holt] Audio Designer and Composer previous in-house at DoubleDown Interactive, [[GameHouse]], Absolute Hero Games, Presence Labs, and more.\n* [[John Romero]] ([[Wolfenstein 3D]], [[Doom (1993 video game)|Doom]], [[Quake (video game)|Quake]])<ref name=\"usgamer\">http://www.usgamer.net/articles/more-than-shamans-and-savages-american-indians-and-game-development</ref> \n* Manuel Marcano ([[BioShock]], [[The Darkness (video game)|The Darkness]], [[Max Payne 3]], Treachery in Beatdown City)<ref name=\"usgamer\"/>\n* Maru Nihoniho, owner of Metia Interactive (Cube)<ref>http://www.maorifuturemakers.com/maru-nihoniho-games-developer</ref>\n* Maize Longboat, creator of [https://maizelongboat.itch.io/terra-nova Terra/Nova]\n* Meagan Byrne, owner of [http://www.achimogames.ca Achimostawinan Games] and original developer of the [[imagineNATIVE]] iNDigital Space. (Hill Agency: PURITY&decay [forthcoming])\n* [https://nathanpowlesslynes.itch.io/ Nathan Powless-Lynes], Mohawk game designer \n* Miranda Due, associate producer at [[Treyarch]] \n* Renee Nejo (Ever Jane, Blood Quantum [forthcoming])\n* [https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephane-nepton-88ba396/ '''St\u00e9phane Nepton :  Innu VFX Artist'''] (Star Wars, Game of Thrones, Far Cry 5, Gears of War 5) and Co-Founder of [https://www.facebook.com/uhulabosnomades/ '''Uhu labos nomades'''],an initiative whose mission is to support the perseverance of schooling among Aboriginal youth through the digital arts.\n\n== Games including Indigenous languages ==\nThere are also numerous video games which include or have been fully translated into Indigenous languages. For example, Pinnguaq has localized osmosis, Ittle Dew and Beneath the Floes.<ref>http://pinnguaq.com/localization/</ref> Both the video games made in the Skins Hawai\u2018i-based workshops, [http://skins.abtec.org/skins5.0/ <nowiki>He Ao Hou [2017]</nowiki>]  and [http://skins.abtec.org/skins6.0/ Wao Kanaka: Realm of the People] [2018], were designed so that the player can play in \u2018\u014clelo Hawai\u2018i as well as in English. \n\n==Academic studies==\n\nAcademic studies of indigenous video gaming are emerging. In 2017, the peer-reviewed open-access Indigenous Studies [[academic journal|journal]] ''Transmotion'' devoted a special issue to the topic.<ref> Transmotion 3:1 (2017) https://journals.kent.ac.uk/index.php/transmotion/issue/view/25</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Race and video games]]\n*[[Indigenous Futurisms]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|32em}}\n\n[[Category:Indigenous peoples]]\n[[Category:Video game culture]]\n", "text_old": "[[Indigenous people]] have a long history of collaborating on the creation of [[video game]]s.<ref name=\"vimeo.com\">https://vimeo.com/128110465</ref> It has only been with the release of [[Never Alone (video game)|Never Alone]] though that broad media attention has been paid to these projects.<ref>A Tribe Called Geek's third podcast called \"Indigenous Gaming\" http://atribecalledgeek.com/tag/video-games/ ; see also http://ca.ign.com/articles/2015/01/16/the-rise-of-indigenous-storytelling-in-games</ref> There have been a growing number of game gatherings and community organizing around Indigenous games happening in the United States, Canada, and New Zealand.<ref name=\"linkedin.com\">https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/natives-game-dev-gathering-elizabeth-lapens%C3%A9e</ref><ref name=\"pinnguaq.com\">http://pinnguaq.com/blog-all/120-evening-celebrate</ref> Indigenous creators of video games have been featured in the DIGITAL MEDIA ART+CADE as part of imagineNATIVE<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.imaginenative.org/home/node/4546 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927051603/http://www.imaginenative.org/home/node/4546 |archive-date=2015-09-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and in ''Memories of the Future/Souvenirs du futur'' at SAW Video Media Art Centre in Ottawa.<ref>http://www.sawvideo.com/event/memories-future</ref> Many early video games that depicted Indigenous people misrepresented them and perpetuated negative stereotypes (see [[Custer's Revenge]]).<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/aboriginal/indigenous-video-game-designer-takes-stand-against-custer-s-revenge-1.2851104</ref> Video games created by Indigenous people enable the creators to self-determine how they are represented<ref>http://www.content.alternative.ac.nz/index.php/alternative/article/view/274</ref>.\n\n== Games where Indigenous people represent themselves ==\nIndigenous people have been involved in a range of projects where they have the opportunity to depict themselves. These games range in the style of the collaboration from games that consult with a single Indigenous person to games that are entirely developed and designed by Indigenous people.<ref name=\"vimeo.com\"/>  \n* [[Aboriginal Peoples Television Network]] ([http://animism.com/ Animism] [2010] [http://www.elizabethlapensee.com/#/games/ Mawisowin] [2012], and [http://yourmix.ca/trackjumper.html Your Mix])<ref name=\"elizabethlapensee.com\">http://www.elizabethlapensee.com/#/games/</ref>\n*Aboriginal Territories in Cyberspace [http://www.abtec.org/projects.html Skins Workshops] ([http://skins.abtec.org/skins1.0/ Ots\u00ec:! Rise of the Kanien\u2019keh\u00e1:ka Legends] [2009], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins2.0/ The Adventures of Skahi\u00f2n:hati: Legend of Stone Giant] [2011], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins3.0/ Skahi\u00f2n:hati: Rise of the Kanien\u2019keh\u00e1:ka Legends] [2012], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins4.0/ Ieni\u00e9n:te and the Peacemaker\u2019s Wampum] [2013]<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/aboriginal/story/1.2483001</ref>, [http://skins.abtec.org/skins5.0/ He Ao Hou] [2017], [http://skins.abtec.org/skins6.0/ Wao Kanaka: Realm of the People] [2018])\n* Arviat Code Club ([https://scratch.mit.edu/users/Pinnguaq/ Multiple scratch games] [2014-2015])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pinnguaq.com/nunavut-code-club/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222151058/http://pinnguaq.com/nunavut-code-club/ |archive-date=2015-12-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Black Cherry Digital Productions ([http://www.pathoftheelders.com/index.php Path of the Elders] [2010] in partnership between the Mushkegowuk Cree, Carlton University, and Pinegrove Productions)<ref>http://www.pathoftheelders.com/aboutus</ref> \n* DarianJ ([http://darianj.itch.io/sleep-guardian Sleep Guardian] [2015])<ref>https://www.facebook.com/skins.workshops/?fref=nf</ref>\n* Elizabeth LaPens\u00e9e When Rivers Were Trails [2019], Thunderbird Strike [2017], Coyote Quest [2017] in collaboration with Loretta Todd, Mikan [2017], Honour Water [2016])<ref name=\"eliza